# Filter the rows based on the 'is_training' column
train_data_df = data_df[data_df['is_training'] == 1]
test_data_df = data_df[data_df['is_training'] == 0]

# Create empty lists to store image data and BMI labels
train_images = []
train_bmi_labels = []
test_images = []
test_bmi_labels = []
In [ ]:
from tensorflow.keras.applications.inception_resnet_v2 import preprocess_input
# Iterate through each row in the training data
for index, row in train_data_df.iterrows():
    image_name = row['name']
    image_path = os.path.join(image_dir, image_name)

    # Check if the image file exists
    if not os.path.exists(image_path):
        continue

    # Load and preprocess the image
    image = load_img(image_path, target_size=(160, 160))
    image = img_to_array(image)
    image = preprocess_input(image)  # Normalize the pixel values between 0 and 1

    # Append the image and BMI label to the respective lists
    train_images.append(image)
    train_bmi_labels.append(row['bmi'])

In [ ]:
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator

# Create an image data generator for data augmentation
datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rotation_range=20,
    width_shift_range=0.1,
    height_shift_range=0.1,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip=True,
    vertical_flip=True,
    fill_mode='nearest'
)

# Apply data augmentation and append augmented images and BMI labels
augmented_images = datagen.flow(train_images, train_bmi_labels, batch_size=train_images.shape[0])
train_images_augmented, train_bmi_labels_augmented = next(augmented_images)
train_images = np.concatenate((train_images, train_images_augmented))
train_bmi_labels = np.concatenate((train_bmi_labels, train_bmi_labels_augmented))
In [ ]:
# Split the data into train and validation sets
train_images, val_images, train_bmi_labels, val_bmi_labels = train_test_split(
    train_images, train_bmi_labels, test_size=0.2, random_state=42
)
In [ ]:
# Load the pre-trained FaceNet model
face_net = InceptionResNetV2(include_top=False, weights='imagenet', input_shape=(160, 160, 3), pooling='avg')
In [ ]:
for layer in face_net.layers[:-4]:
    layer.trainable = False

for layer in face_net.layers[-4:]:
    layer.trainable = True
In [ ]:
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Flatten, Dropout

# Create a new model and add the pre-trained FaceNet model
model = Sequential()
model.add(face_net)

# Add dense layers for regression
model.add(Dense(256, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))

# Add additional dense layers with more units
model.add(Dense(64, activation='relu'))
model.add(Dense(32, activation='relu'))

# Add output layer
model.add(Dense(1, activation='linear'))

# Compile the model
model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0001), metrics=['mae'])
In [ ]:
# Train the model

history = model.fit(
train_images, train_bmi_labels,
validation_data=(val_images, val_bmi_labels),
epochs=10, batch_size=32
)
